			<h1 class="project-hero__title">&#8220;We&#8217;ve lost our compass.&#8221; For California&#8217;s most visible mentally ill, is a return to forced treatment a solution — or a false promise?</h1>

			
			
							<div class="project-hero__caption">

											<svg role="img" class="icon icon--camera" aria-label="camera"><use xlink:href="https://calmatters.org/wp-content/themes/thenewsproject/dist/svg/dist/symbol/svg/sprite.symbol.svg#camera"></use></svg>						<span>Mark Rippee, who developed schizophrenia after a traumatic brain injury, has been living on the streets for years. Photo by Anne Wernikoff for CalMatters</span>
									</div>
